# 1. Why Kubernetes?

Docker can run containers.

But Docker **cannot properly manage applications in production**.

Imagine your backend crashes.

Docker

```text
Backend

↓

Stopped

↓

Application Down
```

No automatic recovery.

---

Kubernetes

```text
Backend Pod

↓

Crash

↓

Kubernetes detects

↓

Creates New Pod

↓

Application Continues
```

This is why almost every company uses Kubernetes.

---

